Calculator Using Python in PictoBlox

A simple calculator project developed using Python mode in PictoBlox. This calculator performs basic arithmetic operations through an interactive interface, helping beginners understand Python programming concepts in a visual environment.

Description

This project demonstrates how Python can be used inside PictoBlox to build a functional calculator. Users can perform addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division. The project focuses on core Python concepts such as variables, input handling, conditional statements, and basic logic.

Features

Addition

Subtraction

Multiplication

Division

Interactive user input

Beginner-friendly design

Technologies Used

PictoBlox

Python (PictoBlox Python Mode)

How It Works

User selects an arithmetic operation

Inputs two numbers

Python code processes the operation

Result is displayed on the screen

Concepts Covered

Python variables

Input and output

Conditional statements

Arithmetic operators

How to Run the Project

Open PictoBlox

Switch to Python Mode

Open the project file

Click the Run button to start

Use Case

School projects

Python practice for beginners

Learning Python with block-based tools

Future Enhancements

Add advanced operations

Improve user interface

Add error handling for invalid input
